'''Anthony J. Steinbock''' is an American philosopher and Professor of Philosophy at [[Southern Illinois University Carbondale]]. He is the Director of the [[Phenomenology Research Center]] and Editor-in-Chief of ''[[Continental Philosophy Review]]''.<ref>{{cite web |title=Professor Anthony J. Steinbock |url=http://www.phenomenologyresearchcenter.org/?page_id=115 |website=[[Phenomenology Research Center]] |accessdate=31 July 2018}}</ref> Steinbock is known for his research on [[phenomenology (philosophy)|phenomenology]].<ref>{{cite journal |title=Moral Emotions: Reclaiming the Evidence of the Heart. By Anthony J. Steinbock |journal=[[Perspectives. International Postgraduate Journal of Philosophy]] |date=2016 |volume=6 |issue=1 |pages=58-60 |url=https://www.degruyter.com/downloadpdf/j/pipjp.2016.6.issue-1/pipjp-2016-0007/pipjp-2016-0007.pdf |accessdate=4 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Drummond |first1=John J. |title=Review of Moral Emotions: Reclaiming the Evidence of the Heart |journal=[[Notre Dame Philosophical Reviews]] |date=6 November 2014 |url=https://ndpr.nd.edu/news/moral-emotions-reclaiming-the-evidence-of-the-heart-2/ |accessdate=4 August 2018 |issn=1538-1617}}</ref><ref>{{cite journal |last1=Soffer |first1=Gail |title=Anthony Steinbock: Home and Beyond: Generative Phenomenology After Husserl |journal=[[Husserl Studies]] |date=1997 |volume=14 |issue=2 |pages=153–160 |url=https://philpapers.org/rec/SOFASH |accessdate=4 August 2018}}</ref>
==Books== * ''It’s Not about the Gift: From Givenness to Loving'' (forthcoming 2018) * ''Limit-Phenomena and Phenomenology in Husserl'' (2017) * ''Moral Emotions: Reclaiming the Evidence of the Heart'' (2014)Recipient of the 2015 Symposium Book Award * ''Phenomenology and Mysticism: The Verticality of Religious Experience''Recipient of the 2009 Edward Goodwin Ballard Book Prize in Phenomenology * ''Home and Beyond: Generative Phenomenology after Husserl'' • Translation of Edmund Husserl, Analyses Concerning Passive and Active Syntheses: Lectures on Transcendental Logic, Husserliana Collected Works, IX (Dordrecht: Kluwer Academic Publishers, 2001), pp. 659 + lx “Translator’s Introduction.”
