{{italic title}}
'''''P4W: Prison for Women''''' is a [[Canada|Canadian]] documentary film, directed by [[Janis Cole]] and [[Holly Dale]] and released in 1981.<ref name=sorrow>"Prison for Women captures the sorrow". ''[[The Globe and Mail]]'', September 10, 1981.</ref> The film profiles several female inmates at the [[Prison for Women]] of [[Kingston Penitentiary]].<ref name=sorrow/>

The film premiered at the [[1981 Toronto International Film Festival|1981 Festival of Festivals]],<ref name=sorrow/> and was broadcast by [[CBC Television]] in 1982.<ref>"CBC will air Prison For Women". ''[[The Globe and Mail]]'', July 14, 1982.</ref> The film won the [[Genie Award]] for [[Academy of Canadian Cinema and Television Award for Best Feature Length Documentary|Best Feature Length Documentary]] at the [[3rd Genie Awards]] in 1982.<ref>"Ticket To Heaven top movie". ''[[The Globe and Mail]]'', March 5, 1982.</ref>

When the Prison for Women closed in 2000, Cole wrote a piece for the Toronto newspaper ''[[Now (newspaper)|Now]]'' about her experiences making the film and her hopes for prison reform.<ref>Janis Cole, [https://nowtoronto.com/news/p4w-closes-but-the-scars-remain/ "P4W closes but the scars remain"]. ''[[Now (newspaper)|Now]]'', July 13, 2000.</ref>

